46static unsigned n(__isl_keep isl_space *dim, enum isl_dim_type type)
47{
48 switch (type) {
49 case isl_dim_param: return dim->nparam;
50 case isl_dim_in: return dim->n_in;
51 case isl_dim_out: return dim->n_out;
52 case isl_dim_all: return dim->nparam + dim->n_in + dim->n_out;
53 default: return 0;
54 }
55}
56
57static unsigned pos(__isl_keep isl_space *dim, enum isl_dim_type type)
58{
59 switch (type) {
60 case isl_dim_param: return 1;
61 case isl_dim_in: return 1 + dim->nparam;
62 case isl_dim_out: return 1 + dim->nparam + dim->n_in;
63 default: return 0;
64 }
65}
66
67unsigned isl_basic_map_dim(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
68 enum isl_dim_type type)
69{
70 if (!bmap)
71 return 0;
72 switch (type) {
73 case isl_dim_cst: return 1;
74 case isl_dim_param:
75 case isl_dim_in:
76 case isl_dim_out: return isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, type);
77 case isl_dim_div: return bmap->n_div;
78 case isl_dim_all: return isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
79 default: return 0;
80 }
81}
82
83unsigned isl_map_dim(__isl_keep isl_map *map, enum isl_dim_type type)
84{
85 return map ? n(map->dim, type) : 0;
86}
87
88unsigned isl_set_dim(__isl_keep isl_setisl_map *set, enum isl_dim_type type)
89{
90 return set ? n(set->dim, type) : 0;
91}
92
93unsigned isl_basic_map_offset(struct isl_basic_map *bmap,
94 enum isl_dim_type type)
95{
96 isl_space *space;
97
98 if (!bmap)
99 return 0;
100
101 space = bmap->dim;
102 switch (type) {
103 case isl_dim_cst: return 0;
104 case isl_dim_param: return 1;
105 case isl_dim_in: return 1 + space->nparam;
106 case isl_dim_out: return 1 + space->nparam + space->n_in;
107 case isl_dim_div: return 1 + space->nparam + space->n_in +
108 space->n_out;
109 default: return 0;
110 }
111}

114 enum isl_dim_type type)
115{
116 return isl_basic_map_offset(bset, type);
117}

197int isl_map_compatible_domain(struct isl_map *map, struct isl_setisl_map *set)
198{
199 int m;
200 if (!map || !set)
201 return -1;
202 m = isl_space_match(map->dim, isl_dim_param, set->dim, isl_dim_param);
203 if (m < 0 || !m)
204 return m;
205 return isl_space_tuple_is_equal(map->dim, isl_dim_in,
206 set->dim, isl_dim_set);
207}
208
209isl_bool isl_basic_map_compatible_domain(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
210 __isl_keep isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset)
211{
212 isl_bool m;
213 if (!bmap || !bset)
214 return isl_bool_error;
215 m = isl_space_match(bmap->dim, isl_dim_param, bset->dim, isl_dim_param);
216 if (m < 0 || !m)
217 return m;
218 return isl_space_tuple_is_equal(bmap->dim, isl_dim_in,
219 bset->dim, isl_dim_set);
220}

222int isl_map_compatible_range(__isl_keep isl_map *map, __isl_keep isl_setisl_map *set)
223{
224 int m;
225 if (!map || !set)
226 return -1;
227 m = isl_space_match(map->dim, isl_dim_param, set->dim, isl_dim_param);
228 if (m < 0 || !m)

281/* Extract the divs in "bmap" as a matrix.
282 */
283__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_mat *isl_basic_map_get_divs(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap)
284{
285 int i;
286 isl_ctx *ctx;
287 isl_mat *div;
288 unsigned total;
289 unsigned cols;
290
291 if (!bmap)
292 return NULL((void*)0);
293
294 ctx = isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap);
295 total = isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, isl_dim_all);
296 cols = 1 + 1 + total + bmap->n_div;
297 div = isl_mat_alloc(ctx, bmap->n_div, cols);
298 if (!div)
299 return NULL((void*)0);
300
301 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_div; ++i)
302 isl_seq_cpy(div->row[i], bmap->div[i], cols);
303
304 return div;
305}
306
307/* Extract the divs in "bset" as a matrix.
308 */
309__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_mat *isl_basic_set_get_divs(__isl_keep isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset)
310{
311 return isl_basic_map_get_divs(bset);
312}

332/* For each known div d = floor(f/m), add the constraints
333 *
334 * f - m d >= 0
335 * -(f-(m-1)) + m d >= 0
336 *
337 * Do not finalize the result.
338 */
339static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *add_known_div_constraints(
340 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap)
341{
342 int i;
343 unsigned n_div;
344
345 if (!bmap)
346 return NULL((void*)0);
347 n_div = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_div);
348 if (n_div == 0)
349 return bmap;
350 bmap = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap);
351 bmap = isl_basic_map_extend_constraints(bmap, 0, 2 * n_div);
352 if (!bmap)
353 return NULL((void*)0);
354 for (i = 0; i < n_div; ++i) {
355 if (isl_int_is_zero(bmap->div[i][0])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->div[i][0])) == 0))
356 continue;
357 if (isl_basic_map_add_div_constraints(bmap, i) < 0)
358 return isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
359 }
360
361 return bmap;
362}
363
364__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_from_local_space(
365 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_local_space *ls)
366{
367 int i;
368 int n_div;
369 isl_basic_map *bmap;
370
371 if (!ls)
372 return NULL((void*)0);
373
374 n_div = isl_local_space_dim(ls, isl_dim_div);
375 bmap = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(isl_local_space_get_space(ls),
376 n_div, 0, 2 * n_div);
377
378 for (i = 0; i < n_div; ++i)
379 if (isl_basic_map_alloc_div(bmap) < 0)
380 goto error;
381
382 for (i = 0; i < n_div; ++i)
383 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->div[i], ls->div->row[i], ls->div->n_col);
384 bmap = add_known_div_constraints(bmap);
385
386 isl_local_space_free(ls);
387 return bmap;
388error:
389 isl_local_space_free(ls);
390 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
391 return NULL((void*)0);
392}

414__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_set_tuple_name(
415 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, enum isl_dim_type type, const char *s)

442__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *isl_map_set_tuple_name(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map,
443 enum isl_dim_type type, const char *s)
444{
445 int i;
446
447 map = isl_map_cow(map);
448 if (!map)
449 return NULL((void*)0);
450
451 map->dim = isl_space_set_tuple_name(map->dim, type, s);
452 if (!map->dim)
453 goto error;
454
455 for (i = 0; i < map->n; ++i) {
456 map->p[i] = isl_basic_map_set_tuple_name(map->p[i], type, s);
457 if (!map->p[i])
458 goto error;
459 }
460
461 return map;
462error:
463 isl_map_free(map);
464 return NULL((void*)0);
465}

469__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_set_tuple_id(
470 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap,

614const char *isl_map_get_dim_name(__isl_keep isl_map *map,

812int isl_basic_map_is_rational(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap)
813{
814 if (!bmap)
815 return -1;
816 return ISL_F_ISSET(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_RATIONAL)(!!(((bmap)->flags) & ((1 << 4))));
817}

820{
821 return isl_basic_map_is_rational(bset);
822}
823
824/* Does "bmap" contain any rational points?
825 *
826 * If "bmap" has an equality for each dimension, equating the dimension
827 * to an integer constant, then it has no rational points, even if it
828 * is marked as rational.
829 */
830int isl_basic_map_has_rational(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap)
831{
832 int has_rational = 1;
833 unsigned total;
834
835 if (!bmap)
836 return -1;
837 if (isl_basic_map_plain_is_empty(bmap))
838 return 0;
839 if (!isl_basic_map_is_rational(bmap))
840 return 0;
841 bmap = isl_basic_map_copy(bmap);
842 bmap = isl_basic_map_implicit_equalities(bmap);
843 if (!bmap)
844 return -1;
845 total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
846 if (bmap->n_eq == total) {
847 int i, j;
848 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_eq; ++i) {
849 j = isl_seq_first_non_zero(bmap->eq[i] + 1, total);
850 if (j < 0)
851 break;
852 if (!isl_int_is_one(bmap->eq[i][1 + j])(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(bmap->eq[i][1 + j]), 1) == 0) &&
853 !isl_int_is_negone(bmap->eq[i][1 + j])(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(bmap->eq[i][1 + j]), -1) == 0))
854 break;
855 j = isl_seq_first_non_zero(bmap->eq[i] + 1 + j + 1,
856 total - j - 1);
857 if (j >= 0)
858 break;
859 }
860 if (i == bmap->n_eq)
861 has_rational = 0;
862 }
863 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
864
865 return has_rational;
866}
867
868/* Does "map" contain any rational points?
869 */
870int isl_map_has_rational(__isl_keep isl_map *map)
871{
872 int i;
873 int has_rational;
874
875 if (!map)
876 return -1;
877 for (i = 0; i < map->n; ++i) {
878 has_rational = isl_basic_map_has_rational(map->p[i]);
879 if (has_rational < 0)
880 return -1;
881 if (has_rational)
882 return 1;
883 }
884 return 0;
885}
886
887/* Does "set" contain any rational points?
888 */
889int isl_set_has_rational(__isl_keep isl_setisl_map *set)
890{
891 return isl_map_has_rational(set);
892}

923static struct isl_basic_map *basic_map_init(struct isl_ctx *ctx,
924 struct isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned extra,
925 unsigned n_eq, unsigned n_ineq)
926{
927 int i;
928 size_t row_size = 1 + isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, isl_dim_all) + extra;
929
930 bmap->ctx = ctx;
931 isl_ctx_ref(ctx);
932
933 bmap->block = isl_blk_alloc(ctx, (n_ineq + n_eq) * row_size);
934 if (isl_blk_is_error(bmap->block))
935 goto error;
936
937 bmap->ineq = isl_alloc_array(ctx, isl_int *, n_ineq + n_eq)((isl_int * *)isl_malloc_or_die(ctx, (n_ineq + n_eq)*sizeof(isl_int
*)));
938 if ((n_ineq + n_eq) && !bmap->ineq)
939 goto error;
940
941 if (extra == 0) {
942 bmap->block2 = isl_blk_empty();
943 bmap->div = NULL((void*)0);
944 } else {
945 bmap->block2 = isl_blk_alloc(ctx, extra * (1 + row_size));
946 if (isl_blk_is_error(bmap->block2))
947 goto error;
948
949 bmap->div = isl_alloc_array(ctx, isl_int *, extra)((isl_int * *)isl_malloc_or_die(ctx, (extra)*sizeof(isl_int *
)));
950 if (!bmap->div)
951 goto error;
952 }
953
954 for (i = 0; i < n_ineq + n_eq; ++i)
955 bmap->ineq[i] = bmap->block.data + i * row_size;
956
957 for (i = 0; i < extra; ++i)
958 bmap->div[i] = bmap->block2.data + i * (1 + row_size);
959
960 bmap->ref = 1;
961 bmap->flags = 0;
962 bmap->c_size = n_eq + n_ineq;
963 bmap->eq = bmap->ineq + n_ineq;
964 bmap->extra = extra;
965 bmap->n_eq = 0;
966 bmap->n_ineq = 0;
967 bmap->n_div = 0;
968 bmap->sample = NULL((void*)0);
969
970 return bmap;
971error:
972 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
973 return NULL((void*)0);
974}

976struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_basic_set_alloc(struct isl_ctx *ctx,
977 unsigned nparam, unsigned dim, unsigned extra,
978 unsigned n_eq, unsigned n_ineq)
979{
980 struct isl_basic_map *bmap;
981 isl_space *space;
982
983 space = isl_space_set_alloc(ctx, nparam, dim);
984 if (!space)
985 return NULL((void*)0);
986
987 bmap = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(space, extra, n_eq, n_ineq);
988 return (struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *)bmap;
989}

991struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_basic_set_alloc_space(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dim,
992 unsigned extra, unsigned n_eq, unsigned n_ineq)
993{
994 struct isl_basic_map *bmap;
995 if (!dim)
996 return NULL((void*)0);
997 isl_assert(dim->ctx, dim->n_in == 0, goto error)do { if (dim->n_in == 0) break; do { isl_handle_error(dim->
ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \"" "dim->n_in == 0" "\" failed"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 997); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
998 bmap = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(dim, extra, n_eq, n_ineq);
999 return (struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *)bmap;
1000error:
1001 isl_space_free(dim);
1002 return NULL((void*)0);
1003}
1004
1005struct isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_alloc_space(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dim,
1006 unsigned extra, unsigned n_eq, unsigned n_ineq)
1007{
1008 struct isl_basic_map *bmap;
1009
1010 if (!dim)
1011 return NULL((void*)0);
1012 bmap = isl_calloc_type(dim->ctx, struct isl_basic_map)((struct isl_basic_map *)isl_calloc_or_die(dim->ctx, 1, sizeof
(struct isl_basic_map)));
1013 if (!bmap)
1014 goto error;
1015 bmap->dim = dim;
1016
1017 return basic_map_init(dim->ctx, bmap, extra, n_eq, n_ineq);
1018error:
1019 isl_space_free(dim);
1020 return NULL((void*)0);
1021}

1023struct isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_alloc(struct isl_ctx *ctx,
1024 unsigned nparam, unsigned in, unsigned out, unsigned extra,
1025 unsigned n_eq, unsigned n_ineq)
1026{
1027 struct isl_basic_map *bmap;
1028 isl_space *dim;
1029
1030 dim = isl_space_alloc(ctx, nparam, in, out);
1031 if (!dim)
1032 return NULL((void*)0);
1033
1034 bmap = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(dim, extra, n_eq, n_ineq);
1035 return bmap;
1036}
1037
1038static void dup_constraints(
1039 struct isl_basic_map *dst, struct isl_basic_map *src)
1040{
1041 int i;
1042 unsigned total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(src);
1043
1044 for (i = 0; i < src->n_eq; ++i) {
1045 int j = isl_basic_map_alloc_equality(dst);
1046 isl_seq_cpy(dst->eq[j], src->eq[i], 1+total);
1047 }
1048
1049 for (i = 0; i < src->n_ineq; ++i) {
1050 int j = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(dst);
1051 isl_seq_cpy(dst->ineq[j], src->ineq[i], 1+total);
1052 }
1053
1054 for (i = 0; i < src->n_div; ++i) {
1055 int j = isl_basic_map_alloc_div(dst);
1056 isl_seq_cpy(dst->div[j], src->div[i], 1+1+total);
1057 }
1058 ISL_F_SET(dst, ISL_BASIC_SET_FINAL)(((dst)->flags) |= ((1 << 0)));
1059}
1060
1061struct isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_dup(struct isl_basic_map *bmap)
1062{
1063 struct isl_basic_map *dup;
1064
1065 if (!bmap)
1066 return NULL((void*)0);
1067 dup = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(isl_space_copy(bmap->dim),
1068 bmap->n_div, bmap->n_eq, bmap->n_ineq);
1069 if (!dup)
1070 return NULL((void*)0);
1071 dup_constraints(dup, bmap);
1072 dup->flags = bmap->flags;
1073 dup->sample = isl_vec_copy(bmap->sample);
1074 return dup;
1075}
1076
1077struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_basic_set_dup(struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset)
1078{
1079 struct isl_basic_map *dup;
1080
1081 dup = isl_basic_map_dup((struct isl_basic_map *)bset);
1082 return (struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *)dup;
1083}

1085struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_basic_set_copy(struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset)
1086{
1087 if (!bset)
1088 return NULL((void*)0);
1089
1090 if (ISL_F_ISSET(bset, ISL_BASIC_SET_FINAL)(!!(((bset)->flags) & ((1 << 0))))) {
1091 bset->ref++;
1092 return bset;
1093 }
1094 return isl_basic_set_dup(bset);
1095}

1097struct isl_setisl_map *isl_set_copy(struct isl_setisl_map *set)

1099 if (!set)
1100 return NULL((void*)0);
1101
1102 set->ref++;
1103 return set;
1104}
1105
1106struct isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_copy(struct isl_basic_map *bmap)
1107{
1108 if (!bmap)
1109 return NULL((void*)0);
1110
1111 if (ISL_F_ISSET(bmap, ISL_BASIC_SET_FINAL)(!!(((bmap)->flags) & ((1 << 0))))) {
1112 bmap->ref++;
1113 return bmap;
1114 }
1115 bmap = isl_basic_map_dup(bmap);
1116 if (bmap)
1117 ISL_F_SET(bmap, ISL_BASIC_SET_FINAL)(((bmap)->flags) |= ((1 << 0)));
1118 return bmap;
1119}

1123 if (!map)
1124 return NULL((void*)0);
1125
1126 map->ref++;
1127 return map;
1128}

1130__isl_null isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_free(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap)
1131{
1132 if (!bmap)
1133 return NULL((void*)0);
1134
1135 if (--bmap->ref > 0)
1136 return NULL((void*)0);
1137
1138 isl_ctx_deref(bmap->ctx);
1139 free(bmap->div);
1140 isl_blk_free(bmap->ctx, bmap->block2);
1141 free(bmap->ineq);
1142 isl_blk_free(bmap->ctx, bmap->block);
1143 isl_vec_free(bmap->sample);
1144 isl_space_free(bmap->dim);
1145 free(bmap);
1146
1147 return NULL((void*)0);
1148}

1150__isl_null isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_basic_set_free(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset)
1151{
1152 return isl_basic_map_free((struct isl_basic_map *)bset);
1153}

1155static int room_for_con(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned n)
1156{
1157 return bmap->n_eq + bmap->n_ineq + n <= bmap->c_size;
1158}

1160__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *isl_map_align_params_map_map_and(
1161 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map2,
1162 __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *(*fn)(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map1,
1163 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map2))
1164{
1165 if (!map1 || !map2)
1166 goto error;
1167 if (isl_space_match(map1->dim, isl_dim_param, map2->dim, isl_dim_param))
1168 return fn(map1, map2);
1169 if (!isl_space_has_named_params(map1->dim) ||
1170 !isl_space_has_named_params(map2->dim))
1171 isl_die(map1->ctx, isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(map1->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "unaligned unnamed parameters"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1172); goto error; } while (0)
1172 "unaligned unnamed parameters", goto error)do { isl_handle_error(map1->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "unaligned unnamed parameters"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1172); goto error; } while (0);
1173 map1 = isl_map_align_params(map1, isl_map_get_space(map2));
1174 map2 = isl_map_align_params(map2, isl_map_get_space(map1));
1175 return fn(map1, map2);
1176error:
1177 isl_map_free(map1);
1178 isl_map_free(map2);
1179 return NULL((void*)0);
1180}
1181
1182isl_bool isl_map_align_params_map_map_and_test(__isl_keep isl_map *map1,
1183 __isl_keep isl_map *map2,
1184 isl_bool (*fn)(__isl_keep isl_map *map1, __isl_keep isl_map *map2))
1185{
1186 isl_bool r;
1187
1188 if (!map1 || !map2)
1189 return isl_bool_error;
1190 if (isl_space_match(map1->dim, isl_dim_param, map2->dim, isl_dim_param))
1191 return fn(map1, map2);
1192 if (!isl_space_has_named_params(map1->dim) ||
1193 !isl_space_has_named_params(map2->dim))
1194 isl_die(map1->ctx, isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(map1->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "unaligned unnamed parameters"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1195); return isl_bool_error; } while (0)
1195 "unaligned unnamed parameters", return isl_bool_error)do { isl_handle_error(map1->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "unaligned unnamed parameters"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1195); return isl_bool_error; } while (0);
1196 map1 = isl_map_copy(map1);
1197 map2 = isl_map_copy(map2);
1198 map1 = isl_map_align_params(map1, isl_map_get_space(map2));
1199 map2 = isl_map_align_params(map2, isl_map_get_space(map1));
1200 r = fn(map1, map2);
1201 isl_map_free(map1);
1202 isl_map_free(map2);
1203 return r;
1204}

1206int isl_basic_map_alloc_equality(struct isl_basic_map *bmap)
1207{
1208 struct isl_ctx *ctx;
1209 if (!bmap)
1210 return -1;
1211 ctx = bmap->ctx;
1212 isl_assert(ctx, room_for_con(bmap, 1), return -1)do { if (room_for_con(bmap, 1)) break; do { isl_handle_error(
ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \"" "room_for_con(bmap, 1)"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1212); return -1; } while (0); } while (0);
1213 isl_assert(ctx, (bmap->eq - bmap->ineq) + bmap->n_eq <= bmap->c_size,do { if ((bmap->eq - bmap->ineq) + bmap->n_eq <= bmap
->c_size) break; do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_unknown
, "Assertion \"" "(bmap->eq - bmap->ineq) + bmap->n_eq <= bmap->c_size"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1214); return -1; } while (0); } while (0)
1214 return -1)do { if ((bmap->eq - bmap->ineq) + bmap->n_eq <= bmap
->c_size) break; do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_unknown
, "Assertion \"" "(bmap->eq - bmap->ineq) + bmap->n_eq <= bmap->c_size"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1214); return -1; } while (0); } while (0);
1215 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 5)));
1216 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NO_REDUNDANT)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 3)));
1217 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NO_IMPLICIT)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 2)));
1218 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_ALL_EQUALITIES)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 7)));
1219 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED_DIVS)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 6)));
1220 if ((bmap->eq - bmap->ineq) + bmap->n_eq == bmap->c_size) {
1221 isl_int *t;
1222 int j = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(bmap);
1223 if (j < 0)
1224 return -1;
1225 t = bmap->ineq[j];
1226 bmap->ineq[j] = bmap->ineq[bmap->n_ineq - 1];
1227 bmap->ineq[bmap->n_ineq - 1] = bmap->eq[-1];
1228 bmap->eq[-1] = t;
1229 bmap->n_eq++;
1230 bmap->n_ineq--;
1231 bmap->eq--;
1232 return 0;
1233 }
1234 isl_seq_clr(bmap->eq[bmap->n_eq] + 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap),
1235 bmap->extra - bmap->n_div);
1236 return bmap->n_eq++;
1237}

1262 return -1;

1279/* Turn inequality "pos" of "bmap" into an equality.
1280 *
1281 * In particular, we move the inequality in front of the equalities
1282 * and move the last inequality in the position of the moved inequality.
1283 * Note that isl_tab_make_equalities_explicit depends on this particular
1284 * change in the ordering of the constraints.
1285 */
1286void isl_basic_map_inequality_to_equality(
1287 struct isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned pos)
1288{
1289 isl_int *t;
1290
1291 t = bmap->ineq[pos];
1292 bmap->ineq[pos] = bmap->ineq[bmap->n_ineq - 1];
1293 bmap->ineq[bmap->n_ineq - 1] = bmap->eq[-1];
1294 bmap->eq[-1] = t;
1295 bmap->n_eq++;
1296 bmap->n_ineq--;
1297 bmap->eq--;
1298 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NO_REDUNDANT)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 3)));
1299 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 5)));
1300 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED_DIVS)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 6)));
1301 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_ALL_EQUALITIES)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 7)));
1302}

1304static int room_for_ineq(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned n)
1305{
1306 return bmap->n_ineq + n <= bmap->eq - bmap->ineq;
1307}

1309int isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(struct isl_basic_map *bmap)
1310{
1311 struct isl_ctx *ctx;
1312 if (!bmap)
1313 return -1;
1314 ctx = bmap->ctx;
1315 isl_assert(ctx, room_for_ineq(bmap, 1), return -1)do { if (room_for_ineq(bmap, 1)) break; do { isl_handle_error
(ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \"" "room_for_ineq(bmap, 1)"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1315); return -1; } while (0); } while (0);
1316 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NO_IMPLICIT)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 2)));
1317 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NO_REDUNDANT)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 3)));
1318 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 5)));
1319 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_ALL_EQUALITIES)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 7)));
1320 isl_seq_clr(bmap->ineq[bmap->n_ineq] +
1321 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap),
1322 bmap->extra - bmap->n_div);
1323 return bmap->n_ineq++;
1324}

1367__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_add_eq(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap,
1368 isl_int *eq)
1369{
1370 int k;
1371
1372 bmap = isl_basic_map_extend_constraints(bmap, 1, 0);
1373 if (!bmap)
1374 return NULL((void*)0);
1375 k = isl_basic_map_alloc_equality(bmap);
1376 if (k < 0)
1377 goto error;
1378 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->eq[k], eq, 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap));
1379 return bmap;
1380error:
1381 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
1382 return NULL((void*)0);
1383}

1386 isl_int *eq)

1392__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_add_ineq(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap,
1393 isl_int *ineq)
1394{

1396

1398 if (!bmap)
1399 return NULL((void*)0);
1400 k = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(bmap);
1401 if (k < 0)
1402 goto error;
1403 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->ineq[k], ineq, 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap));
1404 return bmap;
1405error:
1406 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
1407 return NULL((void*)0);
1408}

1418{
1419 if (!bmap)
1420 return -1;
1421 isl_assert(bmap->ctx, bmap->n_div < bmap->extra, return -1)do { if (bmap->n_div < bmap->extra) break; do { isl_handle_error
(bmap->ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \"" "bmap->n_div < bmap->extra"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1421); return -1; } while (0); } while (0);
1422 isl_seq_clr(bmap->div[bmap->n_div] +
1423 1 + 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap),
1424 bmap->extra - bmap->n_div);
1425 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED_DIVS)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 6)));

1434/* Insert an extra integer division, prescribed by "div", to "bmap"
1435 * at (integer division) position "pos".
1436 *
1437 * The integer division is first added at the end and then moved
1438 * into the right position.
1439 */
1440__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_insert_div(
1441 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, int pos, __isl_keep isl_vec *div)
1442{
1443 int i, k, n_div;
1444
1445 bmap = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap);
1446 if (!bmap || !div)
1447 return isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
1448
1449 if (div->size != 1 + 1 + isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_all))
1450 isl_die(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), isl_error_invalid
, "unexpected size", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1451); return isl_basic_map_free(bmap); } while (0)
1451 "unexpected size", return isl_basic_map_free(bmap))do { isl_handle_error(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), isl_error_invalid
, "unexpected size", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1451); return isl_basic_map_free(bmap); } while (0);
1452 n_div = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_div);
1453 if (pos < 0 || pos > n_div)
1454 isl_die(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), isl_error_invalid
, "invalid position", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1455); return isl_basic_map_free(bmap); } while (0)
1455 "invalid position", return isl_basic_map_free(bmap))do { isl_handle_error(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), isl_error_invalid
, "invalid position", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1455); return isl_basic_map_free(bmap); } while (0);
1456
1457 bmap = isl_basic_map_extend_space(bmap,
1458 isl_basic_map_get_space(bmap), 1, 0, 2);
1459 k = isl_basic_map_alloc_div(bmap);
1460 if (k < 0)
1461 return isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
1462 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->div[k], div->el, div->size);
1463 isl_int_set_si(bmap->div[k][div->size], 0)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->div[k][div->size]), 0);
1464
1465 for (i = k; i > pos; --i)
1466 isl_basic_map_swap_div(bmap, i, i - 1);
1467
1468 return bmap;
1469}

"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"

1484
1485/* Copy constraint from src to dst, putting the vars of src at offset
1486 * dim_off in dst and the divs of src at offset div_off in dst.
1487 * If both sets are actually map, then dim_off applies to the input
1488 * variables.
1489 */
1490static void copy_constraint(struct isl_basic_map *dst_map, isl_int *dst,
1491 struct isl_basic_map *src_map, isl_int *src,
1492 unsigned in_off, unsigned out_off, unsigned div_off)
1493{
1494 unsigned src_nparam = isl_basic_map_n_param(src_map);
1495 unsigned dst_nparam = isl_basic_map_n_param(dst_map);
1496 unsigned src_in = isl_basic_map_n_in(src_map);
1497 unsigned dst_in = isl_basic_map_n_in(dst_map);
1498 unsigned src_out = isl_basic_map_n_out(src_map);
1499 unsigned dst_out = isl_basic_map_n_out(dst_map);
1500 isl_int_set(dst[0], src[0])isl_sioimath_set((dst[0]), *(src[0]));
1501 isl_seq_cpy(dst+1, src+1, isl_min(dst_nparam, src_nparam)((dst_nparam < src_nparam) ? (dst_nparam) : (src_nparam)));
1502 if (dst_nparam > src_nparam)
1503 isl_seq_clr(dst+1+src_nparam,
1504 dst_nparam - src_nparam);
1505 isl_seq_clr(dst+1+dst_nparam, in_off);
1506 isl_seq_cpy(dst+1+dst_nparam+in_off,
1507 src+1+src_nparam,
1508 isl_min(dst_in-in_off, src_in)((dst_in-in_off < src_in) ? (dst_in-in_off) : (src_in)));
1509 if (dst_in-in_off > src_in)
1510 isl_seq_clr(dst+1+dst_nparam+in_off+src_in,
1511 dst_in - in_off - src_in);
1512 isl_seq_clr(dst+1+dst_nparam+dst_in, out_off);
1513 isl_seq_cpy(dst+1+dst_nparam+dst_in+out_off,
1514 src+1+src_nparam+src_in,
1515 isl_min(dst_out-out_off, src_out)((dst_out-out_off < src_out) ? (dst_out-out_off) : (src_out
)));
1516 if (dst_out-out_off > src_out)
1517 isl_seq_clr(dst+1+dst_nparam+dst_in+out_off+src_out,
1518 dst_out - out_off - src_out);
1519 isl_seq_clr(dst+1+dst_nparam+dst_in+dst_out, div_off);
1520 isl_seq_cpy(dst+1+dst_nparam+dst_in+dst_out+div_off,
1521 src+1+src_nparam+src_in+src_out,
1522 isl_min(dst_map->extra-div_off, src_map->n_div)((dst_map->extra-div_off < src_map->n_div) ? (dst_map
->extra-div_off) : (src_map->n_div)));
1523 if (dst_map->n_div-div_off > src_map->n_div)
1524 isl_seq_clr(dst+1+dst_nparam+dst_in+dst_out+
1525 div_off+src_map->n_div,
1526 dst_map->n_div - div_off - src_map->n_div);
1527}
1528
1529static void copy_div(struct isl_basic_map *dst_map, isl_int *dst,
1530 struct isl_basic_map *src_map, isl_int *src,
1531 unsigned in_off, unsigned out_off, unsigned div_off)
1532{
1533 isl_int_set(dst[0], src[0])isl_sioimath_set((dst[0]), *(src[0]));
1534 copy_constraint(dst_map, dst+1, src_map, src+1, in_off, out_off, div_off);
1535}
1536
1537static struct isl_basic_map *add_constraints(struct isl_basic_map *bmap1,
1538 struct isl_basic_map *bmap2, unsigned i_pos, unsigned o_pos)
1539{
1540 int i;
1541 unsigned div_off;
1542
1543 if (!bmap1 || !bmap2)
1544 goto error;
1545
1546 div_off = bmap1->n_div;
1547
1548 for (i = 0; i < bmap2->n_eq; ++i) {
1549 int i1 = isl_basic_map_alloc_equality(bmap1);
1550 if (i1 < 0)
1551 goto error;
1552 copy_constraint(bmap1, bmap1->eq[i1], bmap2, bmap2->eq[i],
1553 i_pos, o_pos, div_off);
1554 }
1555
1556 for (i = 0; i < bmap2->n_ineq; ++i) {
1557 int i1 = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(bmap1);
1558 if (i1 < 0)
1559 goto error;
1560 copy_constraint(bmap1, bmap1->ineq[i1], bmap2, bmap2->ineq[i],
1561 i_pos, o_pos, div_off);
1562 }
1563

1576error:

1579 return NULL((void*)0);
1580}

1759static void swap_vars(struct isl_blk blk, isl_int *a,
1760 unsigned a_len, unsigned b_len)
1761{
1762 isl_seq_cpy(blk.data, a+a_len, b_len);
1763 isl_seq_cpy(blk.data+b_len, a, a_len);
1764 isl_seq_cpy(a, blk.data, b_len+a_len);
1765}

1767static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_swap_vars(
1768 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned pos, unsigned n1, unsigned n2)
1769{

1771 struct isl_blk blk;

1776 isl_assert(bmap->ctx,do { if (pos + n1 + n2 <= 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap
)) break; do { isl_handle_error(bmap->ctx, isl_error_unknown

"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1777); goto error; } while (0); } while (0)
1777 pos + n1 + n2 <= 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap), goto error)do { if (pos + n1 + n2 <= 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap
)) break; do { isl_handle_error(bmap->ctx, isl_error_unknown
, "Assertion \"" "pos + n1 + n2 <= 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap)"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 1777); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
1778
1779 if (n1 == 0 || n2 == 0)
1780 return bmap;
1781

1783 if (!bmap)
1784 return NULL((void*)0);
1785
1786 blk = isl_blk_alloc(bmap->ctx, n1 + n2);
1787 if (isl_blk_is_error(blk))

1804 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_SET_NORMALIZED)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 5)));
1805 bmap = isl_basic_map_gauss(bmap, NULL((void*)0));

1845/* Swap divs "a" and "b" in "bmap" (without modifying any of the constraints
1846 * of "bmap").
1847 */
1848static void swap_div(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap, int a, int b)
1849{
1850 isl_int *t = bmap->div[a];
1851 bmap->div[a] = bmap->div[b];
1852 bmap->div[b] = t;
1853}

1+off+b]));
1867
1868 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_ineq; ++i)

[i][1+off+b]));

[i][1+1+off+b]));

1874}

, 1900); goto error; } while (0)
1900 "index out of bounds", goto error)do { isl_handle_error(map->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "index out of bounds"

, 1900); goto error; } while (0);

2008/* Return true if the definition of the given div (recursively) involves
2009 * any of the given variables.
2010 */
2011static int div_involves_vars(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap, int div,
2012 unsigned first, unsigned n)
2013{
2014 int i;
2015 unsigned div_offset = isl_basic_map_offset(bmap, isl_dim_div);
2016
2017 if (isl_int_is_zero(bmap->div[div][0])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->div[div][0])) == 0))
2018 return 0;
2019 if (isl_seq_first_non_zero(bmap->div[div] + 1 + first, n) >= 0)
2020 return 1;
2021
2022 for (i = bmap->n_div - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2023 if (isl_int_is_zero(bmap->div[div][1 + div_offset + i])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->div[div][1 + div_offset + i])) ==
0))
2024 continue;
2025 if (div_involves_vars(bmap, i, first, n))
2026 return 1;
2027 }
2028
2029 return 0;
2030}
2031
2032/* Try and add a lower and/or upper bound on "div" to "bmap"
2033 * based on inequality "i".
2034 * "total" is the total number of variables (excluding the divs).
2035 * "v" is a temporary object that can be used during the calculations.
2036 * If "lb" is set, then a lower bound should be constructed.
2037 * If "ub" is set, then an upper bound should be constructed.
2038 *
2039 * The calling function has already checked that the inequality does not
2040 * reference "div", but we still need to check that the inequality is
2041 * of the right form. We'll consider the case where we want to construct
2042 * a lower bound. The construction of upper bounds is similar.
2043 *
2044 * Let "div" be of the form
2045 *
2046 * q = floor((a + f(x))/d)
2047 *
2048 * We essentially check if constraint "i" is of the form
2049 *
2050 * b + f(x) >= 0
2051 *
2052 * so that we can use it to derive a lower bound on "div".
2053 * However, we allow a slightly more general form
2054 *
2055 * b + g(x) >= 0
2056 *
2057 * with the condition that the coefficients of g(x) - f(x) are all
2058 * divisible by d.
2059 * Rewriting this constraint as
2060 *
2061 * 0 >= -b - g(x)
2062 *
2063 * adding a + f(x) to both sides and dividing by d, we obtain
2064 *
2065 * (a + f(x))/d >= (a-b)/d + (f(x)-g(x))/d
2066 *
2067 * Taking the floor on both sides, we obtain
2068 *
2069 * q >= floor((a-b)/d) + (f(x)-g(x))/d
2070 *
2071 * or
2072 *
2073 * (g(x)-f(x))/d + ceil((b-a)/d) + q >= 0
2074 *
2075 * In the case of an upper bound, we construct the constraint
2076 *
2077 * (g(x)+f(x))/d + floor((b+a)/d) - q >= 0
2078 *
2079 */
2080static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *insert_bounds_on_div_from_ineq(
2081 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, int div, int i,
2082 unsigned total, isl_int v, int lb, int ub)
2083{
2084 int j;
2085
2086 for (j = 0; (lb || ub) && j < total + bmap->n_div; ++j) {
2087 if (lb) {
2088 isl_int_sub(v, bmap->ineq[i][1 + j],isl_sioimath_sub((v), *(bmap->ineq[i][1 + j]), *(bmap->
div[div][1 + 1 + j]))
2089 bmap->div[div][1 + 1 + j])isl_sioimath_sub((v), *(bmap->ineq[i][1 + j]), *(bmap->
div[div][1 + 1 + j]));
2090 lb = isl_int_is_divisible_by(v, bmap->div[div][0])isl_sioimath_is_divisible_by(*(v), *(bmap->div[div][0]));
2091 }
2092 if (ub) {
2093 isl_int_add(v, bmap->ineq[i][1 + j],isl_sioimath_add((v), *(bmap->ineq[i][1 + j]), *(bmap->
div[div][1 + 1 + j]))
2094 bmap->div[div][1 + 1 + j])isl_sioimath_add((v), *(bmap->ineq[i][1 + j]), *(bmap->
div[div][1 + 1 + j]));
2095 ub = isl_int_is_divisible_by(v, bmap->div[div][0])isl_sioimath_is_divisible_by(*(v), *(bmap->div[div][0]));
2096 }
2097 }
2098 if (!lb && !ub)
2099 return bmap;
2100
2101 bmap = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap);
2102 bmap = isl_basic_map_extend_constraints(bmap, 0, lb + ub);
2103 if (lb) {
2104 int k = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(bmap);
2105 if (k < 0)
2106 goto error;
2107 for (j = 0; j < 1 + total + bmap->n_div; ++j) {
2108 isl_int_sub(bmap->ineq[k][j], bmap->ineq[i][j],isl_sioimath_sub((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[i][j]
), *(bmap->div[div][1 + j]))
2109 bmap->div[div][1 + j])isl_sioimath_sub((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[i][j]
), *(bmap->div[div][1 + j]));
2110 isl_int_cdiv_q(bmap->ineq[k][j],isl_sioimath_cdiv_q((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[k]
[j]), *(bmap->div[div][0]))
2111 bmap->ineq[k][j], bmap->div[div][0])isl_sioimath_cdiv_q((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[k]
[j]), *(bmap->div[div][0]));
2112 }
2113 isl_int_set_si(bmap->ineq[k][1 + total + div], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->ineq[k][1 + total + div]), 1);
2114 }
2115 if (ub) {
2116 int k = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(bmap);
2117 if (k < 0)
2118 goto error;
2119 for (j = 0; j < 1 + total + bmap->n_div; ++j) {
2120 isl_int_add(bmap->ineq[k][j], bmap->ineq[i][j],isl_sioimath_add((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[i][j]
), *(bmap->div[div][1 + j]))
2121 bmap->div[div][1 + j])isl_sioimath_add((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[i][j]
), *(bmap->div[div][1 + j]));
2122 isl_int_fdiv_q(bmap->ineq[k][j],isl_sioimath_fdiv_q((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[k]
[j]), *(bmap->div[div][0]))
2123 bmap->ineq[k][j], bmap->div[div][0])isl_sioimath_fdiv_q((bmap->ineq[k][j]), *(bmap->ineq[k]
[j]), *(bmap->div[div][0]));
2124 }
2125 isl_int_set_si(bmap->ineq[k][1 + total + div], -1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->ineq[k][1 + total + div]), -1);
2126 }
2127
2128 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 5)));
2129 return bmap;
2130error:
2131 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
2132 return NULL((void*)0);
2133}
2134
2135/* This function is called right before "div" is eliminated from "bmap"
2136 * using Fourier-Motzkin.
2137 * Look through the constraints of "bmap" for constraints on the argument
2138 * of the integer division and use them to construct constraints on the
2139 * integer division itself. These constraints can then be combined
2140 * during the Fourier-Motzkin elimination.
2141 * Note that it is only useful to introduce lower bounds on "div"
2142 * if "bmap" already contains upper bounds on "div" as the newly
2143 * introduce lower bounds can then be combined with the pre-existing
2144 * upper bounds. Similarly for upper bounds.
2145 * We therefore first check if "bmap" contains any lower and/or upper bounds
2146 * on "div".
2147 *
2148 * It is interesting to note that the introduction of these constraints
2149 * can indeed lead to more accurate results, even when compared to
2150 * deriving constraints on the argument of "div" from constraints on "div".
2151 * Consider, for example, the set
2152 *
2153 * { [i,j,k] : 3 + i + 2j >= 0 and 2 * [(i+2j)/4] <= k }
2154 *
2155 * The second constraint can be rewritten as
2156 *
2157 * 2 * [(-i-2j+3)/4] + k >= 0
2158 *
2159 * from which we can derive
2160 *
2161 * -i - 2j + 3 >= -2k
2162 *
2163 * or
2164 *
2165 * i + 2j <= 3 + 2k
2166 *
2167 * Combined with the first constraint, we obtain
2168 *
2169 * -3 <= 3 + 2k or k >= -3
2170 *
2171 * If, on the other hand we derive a constraint on [(i+2j)/4] from
2172 * the first constraint, we obtain
2173 *
2174 * [(i + 2j)/4] >= [-3/4] = -1
2175 *
2176 * Combining this constraint with the second constraint, we obtain
2177 *
2178 * k >= -2
2179 */
2180static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *insert_bounds_on_div(
2181 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, int div)
2182{
2183 int i;
2184 int check_lb, check_ub;
2185 isl_int v;
2186 unsigned total;
2187
2188 if (!bmap)
2189 return NULL((void*)0);
2190
2191 if (isl_int_is_zero(bmap->div[div][0])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->div[div][0])) == 0))
2192 return bmap;
2193
2194 total = isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, isl_dim_all);
2195
2196 check_lb = 0;
2197 check_ub = 0;
2198 for (i = 0; (!check_lb || !check_ub) && i < bmap->n_ineq; ++i) {
2199 int s = isl_int_sgn(bmap->ineq[i][1 + total + div])isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->ineq[i][1 + total + div]));
2200 if (s > 0)
2201 check_ub = 1;
2202 if (s < 0)
2203 check_lb = 1;
2204 }
2205
2206 if (!check_lb && !check_ub)
2207 return bmap;
2208
2209 isl_int_init(v)isl_sioimath_init((v));
2210
2211 for (i = 0; bmap && i < bmap->n_ineq; ++i) {
2212 if (!isl_int_is_zero(bmap->ineq[i][1 + total + div])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->ineq[i][1 + total + div])) == 0))
2213 continue;
2214
2215 bmap = insert_bounds_on_div_from_ineq(bmap, div, i, total, v,
2216 check_lb, check_ub);
2217 }
2218
2219 isl_int_clear(v)isl_sioimath_clear((v));
2220
2221 return bmap;
2222}

2295/* Does the desciption of "bmap" depend on the specified dimensions?
2296 * We also check whether the dimensions appear in any of the div definitions.
2297 * In principle there is no need for this check. If the dimensions appear
2298 * in a div definition, they also appear in the defining constraints of that
2299 * div.
2300 */
2301isl_bool isl_basic_map_involves_dims(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
2302 enum isl_dim_type type, unsigned first, unsigned n)
2303{
2304 int i;
2305
2306 if (!bmap)
2307 return isl_bool_error;
2308
2309 if (first + n > isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, type))
2310 isl_die(bmap->ctx, isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(bmap->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "index out of bounds"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 2311); return isl_bool_error; } while (0)
2311 "index out of bounds", return isl_bool_error)do { isl_handle_error(bmap->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "index out of bounds"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 2311); return isl_bool_error; } while (0);
2312
2313 first += isl_basic_map_offset(bmap, type);
2314 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_eq; ++i)
2315 if (isl_seq_first_non_zero(bmap->eq[i] + first, n) >= 0)
2316 return isl_bool_true;
2317 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_ineq; ++i)
2318 if (isl_seq_first_non_zero(bmap->ineq[i] + first, n) >= 0)
2319 return isl_bool_true;
2320 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_div; ++i) {
2321 if (isl_int_is_zero(bmap->div[i][0])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->div[i][0])) == 0))
2322 continue;
2323 if (isl_seq_first_non_zero(bmap->div[i] + 1 + first, n) >= 0)
2324 return isl_bool_true;
2325 }
2326
2327 return isl_bool_false;
2328}

2364/* Does local variable "div" of "bmap" have a complete explicit representation?
2365 * Having a complete explicit representation requires not only
2366 * an explicit representation, but also that all local variables
2367 * that appear in this explicit representation in turn have
2368 * a complete explicit representation.
2369 */
2370isl_bool isl_basic_map_div_is_known(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap, int div)
2371{
2372 int i;
2373 unsigned div_offset = isl_basic_map_offset(bmap, isl_dim_div);
2374 isl_bool marked;
2375
2376 marked = isl_basic_map_div_is_marked_unknown(bmap, div);
2377 if (marked < 0 || marked)
2378 return isl_bool_not(marked);
2379
2380 for (i = bmap->n_div - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2381 isl_bool known;
2382
2383 if (isl_int_is_zero(bmap->div[div][1 + div_offset + i])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(bmap->div[div][1 + div_offset + i])) ==
0))
2384 continue;
2385 known = isl_basic_map_div_is_known(bmap, i);
2386 if (known < 0 || !known)
2387 return known;
2388 }
2389
2390 return isl_bool_true;
2391}

2467struct isl_map *isl_map_remove_dims(struct isl_map *map,
2468 enum isl_dim_type type, unsigned first, unsigned n)
2469{
2470 int i;
2471
2472 if (n == 0)
2473 return map;
2474
2475 map = isl_map_cow(map);
2476 if (!map)
2477 return NULL((void*)0);
2478 isl_assert(map->ctx, first + n <= isl_map_dim(map, type), goto error)do { if (first + n <= isl_map_dim(map, type)) break; do { isl_handle_error
(map->ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \"" "first + n <= isl_map_dim(map, type)"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 2478); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
2479
2480 for (i = 0; i < map->n; ++i) {
2481 map->p[i] = isl_basic_map_eliminate_vars(map->p[i],
2482 isl_basic_map_offset(map->p[i], type) - 1 + first, n);
2483 if (!map->p[i])
2484 goto error;
2485 }
2486 map = isl_map_drop(map, type, first, n);
2487 return map;
2488error:
2489 isl_map_free(map);
2490 return NULL((void*)0);
2491}

2506static void dump_term(struct isl_basic_map *bmap,
2507 isl_int c, int pos, FILE *out)
2508{
2509 const char *name;
2510 unsigned in = isl_basic_map_n_in(bmap);
2511 unsigned dim = in + isl_basic_map_n_out(bmap);
2512 unsigned nparam = isl_basic_map_n_param(bmap);
2513 if (!pos)
2514 isl_int_print(out, c, 0)isl_sioimath_print(out, *(c), 0);
2515 else {
2516 if (!isl_int_is_one(c)(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(c), 1) == 0))
2517 isl_int_print(out, c, 0)isl_sioimath_print(out, *(c), 0);
2518 if (pos < 1 + nparam) {
2519 name = isl_space_get_dim_name(bmap->dim,
2520 isl_dim_param, pos - 1);
2521 if (name)
2522 fprintf(out, "%s", name);
2523 else
2524 fprintf(out, "p%d", pos - 1);
2525 } else if (pos < 1 + nparam + in)
2526 fprintf(out, "i%d", pos - 1 - nparam);
2527 else if (pos < 1 + nparam + dim)
2528 fprintf(out, "o%d", pos - 1 - nparam - in);
2529 else
2530 fprintf(out, "e%d", pos - 1 - nparam - dim);
2531 }
2532}
2533
2534static void dump_constraint_sign(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, isl_int *c,
2535 int sign, FILE *out)
2536{
2537 int i;
2538 int first;
2539 unsigned len = 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
2540 isl_int v;
2541
2542 isl_int_init(v)isl_sioimath_init((v));
2543 for (i = 0, first = 1; i < len; ++i) {
2544 if (isl_int_sgn(c[i])isl_sioimath_sgn(*(c[i])) * sign <= 0)
2545 continue;
2546 if (!first)
2547 fprintf(out, " + ");
2548 first = 0;
2549 isl_int_abs(v, c[i])isl_sioimath_abs((v), *(c[i]));
2550 dump_term(bmap, v, i, out);
2551 }
2552 isl_int_clear(v)isl_sioimath_clear((v));
2553 if (first)
2554 fprintf(out, "0");
2555}
2556
2557static void dump_constraint(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, isl_int *c,
2558 const char *op, FILE *out, int indent)
2559{
2560 int i;
2561
2562 fprintf(out, "%*s", indent, "");
2563
2564 dump_constraint_sign(bmap, c, 1, out);
2565 fprintf(out, " %s ", op);
2566 dump_constraint_sign(bmap, c, -1, out);
2567
2568 fprintf(out, "\n");
2569
2570 for (i = bmap->n_div; i < bmap->extra; ++i) {
2571 if (isl_int_is_zero(c[1+isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, isl_dim_all)+i])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(c[1+isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, isl_dim_all
)+i])) == 0))
2572 continue;
2573 fprintf(out, "%*s", indent, "");
2574 fprintf(out, "ERROR: unused div coefficient not zero\n");
2575 abort();
2576 }
2577}
2578
2579static void dump_constraints(struct isl_basic_map *bmap,
2580 isl_int **c, unsigned n,
2581 const char *op, FILE *out, int indent)
2582{
2583 int i;
2584
2585 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i)
2586 dump_constraint(bmap, c[i], op, out, indent);
2587}
2588
2589static void dump_affine(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, isl_int *exp, FILE *out)
2590{
2591 int j;
2592 int first = 1;
2593 unsigned total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
2594
2595 for (j = 0; j < 1 + total; ++j) {
2596 if (isl_int_is_zero(exp[j])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(exp[j])) == 0))
2597 continue;
2598 if (!first && isl_int_is_pos(exp[j])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(exp[j])) > 0))
2599 fprintf(out, "+");
2600 dump_term(bmap, exp[j], j, out);
2601 first = 0;
2602 }
2603}
2604
2605static void dump(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, FILE *out, int indent)
2606{
2607 int i;
2608
2609 dump_constraints(bmap, bmap->eq, bmap->n_eq, "=", out, indent);
2610 dump_constraints(bmap, bmap->ineq, bmap->n_ineq, ">=", out, indent);
2611
2612 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_div; ++i) {
2613 fprintf(out, "%*s", indent, "");
2614 fprintf(out, "e%d = [(", i);
2615 dump_affine(bmap, bmap->div[i]+1, out);
2616 fprintf(out, ")/");
2617 isl_int_print(out, bmap->div[i][0], 0)isl_sioimath_print(out, *(bmap->div[i][0]), 0);
2618 fprintf(out, "]\n");
2619 }
2620}

2655{

2658 return -1;
2659 total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
2660 isl_assert(bmap->ctx, pos < bmap->n_ineq, return -1)do { if (pos < bmap->n_ineq) break; do { isl_handle_error
(bmap->ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \"" "pos < bmap->n_ineq"
"\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 2660); return -1; } while (0); } while (0);
2661 isl_seq_neg(bmap->ineq[pos], bmap->ineq[pos], 1 + total);
2662 isl_int_sub_ui(bmap->ineq[pos][0], bmap->ineq[pos][0], 1)isl_sioimath_sub_ui((bmap->ineq[pos][0]), *(bmap->ineq[
pos][0]), 1);
2663 ISL_F_CLR(bmap, ISL_BASIC_MAP_NORMALIZED)(((bmap)->flags) &= ~((1 << 5)));
2664 return 0;

2695/* Make sure "map" has room for at least "n" more basic maps.
2696 */
2697struct isl_map *isl_map_grow(struct isl_map *map, int n)
2698{
2699 int i;
2700 struct isl_map *grown = NULL((void*)0);
2701
2702 if (!map)
2703 return NULL((void*)0);
2704 isl_assert(map->ctx, n >= 0, goto error)do { if (n >= 0) break; do { isl_handle_error(map->ctx,
isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \"" "n >= 0" "\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 2704); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
2705 if (map->n + n <= map->size)
2706 return map;
2707 grown = isl_map_alloc_space(isl_map_get_space(map), map->n + n, map->flags);
2708 if (!grown)
2709 goto error;
2710 for (i = 0; i < map->n; ++i) {
2711 grown->p[i] = isl_basic_map_copy(map->p[i]);
2712 if (!grown->p[i])
2713 goto error;
2714 grown->n++;
2715 }
2716 isl_map_free(map);
2717 return grown;
2718error:
2719 isl_map_free(grown);
2720 isl_map_free(map);
2721 return NULL((void*)0);
2722}

2745}

2882
2883isl_bool isl_basic_map_contains(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
2884 __isl_keep isl_vec *vec)
2885{
2886 int i;
2887 unsigned total;
2888 isl_int s;
2889
2890 if (!bmap || !vec)
2891 return isl_bool_error;
2892
2893 total = 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
2894 if (total != vec->size)
2895 return isl_bool_error;
2896
2897 isl_int_init(s)isl_sioimath_init((s));
2898
2899 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_eq; ++i) {
2900 isl_seq_inner_product(vec->el, bmap->eq[i], total, &s);
2901 if (!isl_int_is_zero(s)(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(s)) == 0)) {
2902 isl_int_clear(s)isl_sioimath_clear((s));
2903 return isl_bool_false;
2904 }
2905 }
2906
2907 for (i = 0; i < bmap->n_ineq; ++i) {
2908 isl_seq_inner_product(vec->el, bmap->ineq[i], total, &s);
2909 if (isl_int_is_neg(s)(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(s)) < 0)) {
2910 isl_int_clear(s)isl_sioimath_clear((s));
2911 return isl_bool_false;
2912 }
2913 }
2914
2915 isl_int_clear(s)isl_sioimath_clear((s));
2916
2917 return isl_bool_true;
2918}
2919
2920isl_bool isl_basic_set_contains(__isl_keep isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset,
2921 __isl_keep isl_vec *vec)
2922{
2923 return isl_basic_map_contains((struct isl_basic_map *)bset, vec);
2924}

"isl_space_is_equal(bmap1->dim, bmap2->dim)" "\" failed"

, 2945); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
2946
2947 if (isl_basic_map_plain_is_empty(bmap1)) {
2948 isl_basic_map_free(bmap2);
2949 return bmap1;
2950 }
2951 if (isl_basic_map_plain_is_empty(bmap2)) {
2952 isl_basic_map_free(bmap1);
2953 return bmap2;
2954 }
2955
2956 if (bmap1->sample &&
2957 isl_basic_map_contains(bmap1, bmap1->sample) > 0 &&
2958 isl_basic_map_contains(bmap2, bmap1->sample) > 0)
2959 sample = isl_vec_copy(bmap1->sample);
2960 else if (bmap2->sample &&
2961 isl_basic_map_contains(bmap1, bmap2->sample) > 0 &&
2962 isl_basic_map_contains(bmap2, bmap2->sample) > 0)
2963 sample = isl_vec_copy(bmap2->sample);
2964
2965 bmap1 = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap1);
2966 if (!bmap1)
2967 goto error;
2968 bmap1 = isl_basic_map_extend_space(bmap1, isl_space_copy(bmap1->dim),
2969 bmap2->n_div, bmap2->n_eq, bmap2->n_ineq);
2970 bmap1 = add_constraints(bmap1, bmap2, 0, 0);
2971
2972 if (!bmap1)
2973 isl_vec_free(sample);
2974 else if (sample) {
2975 isl_vec_free(bmap1->sample);
2976 bmap1->sample = sample;
2977 }
2978
2979 bmap1 = isl_basic_map_simplify(bmap1);
2980 return isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap1);
2981error:
2982 if (sample)
2983 isl_vec_free(sample);
2984 isl_basic_map_free(bmap1);
2985 isl_basic_map_free(bmap2);
2986 return NULL((void*)0);
2987}

3056/* map2 may be either a parameter domain or a map living in the same
3057 * space as map1.
3058 */
3059static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *map_intersect_internal(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map1,
3060 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map2)
3061{
3062 unsigned flags = 0;
3063 isl_map *result;
3064 int i, j;
3065
3066 if (!map1 || !map2)
3067 goto error;
3068
3069 if ((isl_map_plain_is_empty(map1) ||
3070 isl_map_plain_is_universe(map2)) &&
3071 isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)) {
3072 isl_map_free(map2);
3073 return map1;
3074 }
3075 if ((isl_map_plain_is_empty(map2) ||
3076 isl_map_plain_is_universe(map1)) &&
3077 isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)) {
3078 isl_map_free(map1);
3079 return map2;
3080 }
3081
3082 if (map1->n == 1 && map2->n == 1 &&
3083 map1->p[0]->n_div == 0 && map2->p[0]->n_div == 0 &&
3084 isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim) &&
3085 (map1->p[0]->n_eq + map1->p[0]->n_ineq == 1 ||
3086 map2->p[0]->n_eq + map2->p[0]->n_ineq == 1))
3087 return map_intersect_add_constraint(map1, map2);
3088
3089 if (isl_space_dim(map2->dim, isl_dim_all) !=
3090 isl_space_dim(map2->dim, isl_dim_param))
3091 isl_assert(map1->ctx,do { if (isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)) break
; do { isl_handle_error(map1->ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \""
"isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)" "\" failed"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 3092); goto error; } while (0); } while (0)
3092 isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim), goto error)do { if (isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)) break
; do { isl_handle_error(map1->ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \""
"isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)" "\" failed"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 3092); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
3093
3094 if (ISL_F_ISSET(map1, ISL_MAP_DISJOINT)(!!(((map1)->flags) & ((1 << 0)))) &&
3095 ISL_F_ISSET(map2, ISL_MAP_DISJOINT)(!!(((map2)->flags) & ((1 << 0)))))
3096 ISL_FL_SET(flags, ISL_MAP_DISJOINT)((flags) |= ((1 << 0)));
3097
3098 result = isl_map_alloc_space(isl_space_copy(map1->dim),
3099 map1->n * map2->n, flags);
3100 if (!result)
3101 goto error;
3102 for (i = 0; i < map1->n; ++i)
3103 for (j = 0; j < map2->n; ++j) {
3104 struct isl_basic_map *part;
3105 part = isl_basic_map_intersect(
3106 isl_basic_map_copy(map1->p[i]),
3107 isl_basic_map_copy(map2->p[j]));
3108 if (isl_basic_map_is_empty(part) < 0)
3109 part = isl_basic_map_free(part);
3110 result = isl_map_add_basic_map(result, part);
3111 if (!result)
3112 goto error;
3113 }
3114 isl_map_free(map1);
3115 isl_map_free(map2);
3116 return result;
3117error:
3118 isl_map_free(map1);
3119 isl_map_free(map2);
3120 return NULL((void*)0);
3121}

3172struct isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_reverse(struct isl_basic_map *bmap)
3173{
3174 isl_space *space;
3175 unsigned pos, n1, n2;
3176
3177 if (!bmap)
3178 return NULL((void*)0);
3179 bmap = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap);
3180 if (!bmap)
3181 return NULL((void*)0);
3182 space = isl_space_reverse(isl_space_copy(bmap->dim));
3183 pos = isl_basic_map_offset(bmap, isl_dim_in);
3184 n1 = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_in);
3185 n2 = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_out);
3186 bmap = isl_basic_map_swap_vars(bmap, pos, n1, n2);
3187 return isl_basic_map_reset_space(bmap, space);
3188}

3190static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *basic_map_space_reset(
3191 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, enum isl_dim_type type)
3192{
3193 isl_space *space;
3194
3195 if (!bmap)
3196 return NULL((void*)0);
3197 if (!isl_space_is_named_or_nested(bmap->dim, type))
3198 return bmap;
3199
3200 space = isl_basic_map_get_space(bmap);
3201 space = isl_space_reset(space, type);
3202 bmap = isl_basic_map_reset_space(bmap, space);
3203 return bmap;
3204}

3206__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_insert_dims(
3207 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, enum isl_dim_type type,
3208 unsigned pos, unsigned n)
3209{
3210 isl_space *res_dim;
3211 struct isl_basic_map *res;
3212 struct isl_dim_map *dim_map;
3213 unsigned total, off;
3214 enum isl_dim_type t;
3215
3216 if (n == 0)
3217 return basic_map_space_reset(bmap, type);
3218
3219 if (!bmap)
3220 return NULL((void*)0);
3221
3222 res_dim = isl_space_insert_dims(isl_basic_map_get_space(bmap), type, pos, n);
3223
3224 total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap) + n;
3225 dim_map = isl_dim_map_alloc(bmap->ctx, total);
3226 off = 0;
3227 for (t = isl_dim_param; t <= isl_dim_out; ++t) {
3228 if (t != type) {
3229 isl_dim_map_dim(dim_map, bmap->dim, t, off);
3230 } else {
3231 unsigned size = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, t);
3232 isl_dim_map_dim_range(dim_map, bmap->dim, t,
3233 0, pos, off);
3234 isl_dim_map_dim_range(dim_map, bmap->dim, t,
3235 pos, size - pos, off + pos + n);
3236 }
3237 off += isl_space_dim(res_dim, t);
3238 }
3239 isl_dim_map_div(dim_map, bmap, off);
3240
3241 res = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(res_dim,
3242 bmap->n_div, bmap->n_eq, bmap->n_ineq);
3243 if (isl_basic_map_is_rational(bmap))
3244 res = isl_basic_map_set_rational(res);
3245 if (isl_basic_map_plain_is_empty(bmap)) {
3246 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
3247 free(dim_map);
3248 return isl_basic_map_set_to_empty(res);
3249 }
3250 res = isl_basic_map_add_constraints_dim_map(res, bmap, dim_map);
3251 return isl_basic_map_finalize(res);
3252}

3504/* Move the specified dimensions to the last columns right before
3505 * the divs. Don't change the dimension specification of bmap.
3506 * That's the responsibility of the caller.
3507 */
3508static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *move_last(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap,
3509 enum isl_dim_type type, unsigned first, unsigned n)
3510{
3511 struct isl_dim_map *dim_map;
3512 struct isl_basic_map *res;
3513 enum isl_dim_type t;
3514 unsigned total, off;
3515
3516 if (!bmap)
3517 return NULL((void*)0);
3518 if (pos(bmap->dim, type) + first + n ==
3519 1 + isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, isl_dim_all))
3520 return bmap;
3521
3522 total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
3523 dim_map = isl_dim_map_alloc(bmap->ctx, total);
3524
3525 off = 0;
3526 for (t = isl_dim_param; t <= isl_dim_out; ++t) {
3527 unsigned size = isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, t);
3528 if (t == type) {
3529 isl_dim_map_dim_range(dim_map, bmap->dim, t,
3530 0, first, off);
3531 off += first;
3532 isl_dim_map_dim_range(dim_map, bmap->dim, t,
3533 first, n, total - bmap->n_div - n);
3534 isl_dim_map_dim_range(dim_map, bmap->dim, t,
3535 first + n, size - (first + n), off);
3536 off += size - (first + n);
3537 } else {
3538 isl_dim_map_dim(dim_map, bmap->dim, t, off);
3539 off += size;
3540 }
3541 }
3542 isl_dim_map_div(dim_map, bmap, off + n);
3543
3544 res = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(isl_basic_map_get_space(bmap),
3545 bmap->n_div, bmap->n_eq, bmap->n_ineq);
3546 res = isl_basic_map_add_constraints_dim_map(res, bmap, dim_map);
3547 return res;
3548}
3549
3550/* Insert "n" rows in the divs of "bmap".
3551 *
3552 * The number of columns is not changed, which means that the last
3553 * dimensions of "bmap" are being reintepreted as the new divs.
3554 * The space of "bmap" is not adjusted, however, which means
3555 * that "bmap" is left in an inconsistent state. Removing "n" dimensions
3556 * from the space of "bmap" is the responsibility of the caller.
3557 */
3558static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *insert_div_rows(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap,
3559 int n)
3560{
3561 int i;
3562 size_t row_size;
3563 isl_int **new_div;
3564 isl_int *old;
3565
3566 bmap = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap);
3567 if (!bmap)
3568 return NULL((void*)0);
3569
3570 row_size = 1 + isl_space_dim(bmap->dim, isl_dim_all) + bmap->extra;
3571 old = bmap->block2.data;
3572 bmap->block2 = isl_blk_extend(bmap->ctx, bmap->block2,
3573 (bmap->extra + n) * (1 + row_size));
3574 if (!bmap->block2.data)
3575 return isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
3576 new_div = isl_alloc_array(bmap->ctx, isl_int *, bmap->extra + n)((isl_int * *)isl_malloc_or_die(bmap->ctx, (bmap->extra
+ n)*sizeof(isl_int *)));
3577 if (!new_div)
3578 return isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
3579 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
3580 new_div[i] = bmap->block2.data +
3581 (bmap->extra + i) * (1 + row_size);
3582 isl_seq_clr(new_div[i], 1 + row_size);
3583 }
3584 for (i = 0; i < bmap->extra; ++i)
3585 new_div[n + i] = bmap->block2.data + (bmap->div[i] - old);
3586 free(bmap->div);
3587 bmap->div = new_div;
3588 bmap->n_div += n;
3589 bmap->extra += n;
3590
3591 return bmap;
3592}

3594/* Drop constraints from "bmap" that only involve the variables
3595 * of "type" in the range [first, first + n] that are not related
3596 * to any of the variables outside that interval.
3597 * These constraints cannot influence the values for the variables
3598 * outside the interval, except in case they cause "bmap" to be empty.
3599 * Only drop the constraints if "bmap" is known to be non-empty.
3600 */
3601static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *drop_irrelevant_constraints(
3602 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, enum isl_dim_type type,
3603 unsigned first, unsigned n)
3604{
3605 int i;
3606 int *groups;
3607 unsigned dim, n_div;
3608 isl_bool non_empty;
3609
3610 non_empty = isl_basic_map_plain_is_non_empty(bmap);
3611 if (non_empty < 0)
3612 return isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
3613 if (!non_empty)
3614 return bmap;
3615
3616 dim = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_all);
3617 n_div = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_div);
3618 groups = isl_calloc_array(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), int, dim)((int *)isl_calloc_or_die(isl_basic_map_get_ctx(bmap), dim, sizeof
(int)));
3619 if (!groups)
3620 return isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
3621 first += isl_basic_map_offset(bmap, type) - 1;
3622 for (i = 0; i < first; ++i)
3623 groups[i] = -1;
3624 for (i = first + n; i < dim - n_div; ++i)
3625 groups[i] = -1;
3626
3627 bmap = isl_basic_map_drop_unrelated_constraints(bmap, groups);
3628
3629 return bmap;
3630}

3764static struct isl_basic_map *add_divs(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned n)
3765{
3766 int i, j;
3767
3768 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
3769 j = isl_basic_map_alloc_div(bmap);
3770 if (j < 0)
3771 goto error;
3772 isl_seq_clr(bmap->div[j], 1+1+isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap));
3773 }
3774 return bmap;
3775error:
3776 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
3777 return NULL((void*)0);
3778}

3780struct isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_apply_range(
3781 struct isl_basic_map *bmap1, struct isl_basic_map *bmap2)

3787
3788 if (!bmap1 || !bmap2)
3789 goto error;
3790 if (!isl_space_match(bmap1->dim, isl_dim_param,

3873/* Given two basic maps A -> f(A) and B -> g(B), construct a basic map
3874 * A \cap B -> f(A) + f(B)

"isl_space_is_equal(bmap1->dim, bmap2->dim)" "\" failed"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 3888); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
3889

3932/* Given two maps A -> f(A) and B -> g(B), construct a map
3933 * A \cap B -> f(A) + f(B)
3934 */
3935struct isl_map *isl_map_sum(struct isl_map *map1, struct isl_map *map2)
3936{
3937 struct isl_map *result;
3938 int i, j;
3939
3940 if (!map1 || !map2)
3941 goto error;
3942
3943 isl_assert(map1->ctx, isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim), goto error)do { if (isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)) break
; do { isl_handle_error(map1->ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \""
"isl_space_is_equal(map1->dim, map2->dim)" "\" failed"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 3943); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
3944
3945 result = isl_map_alloc_space(isl_space_copy(map1->dim),
3946 map1->n * map2->n, 0);
3947 if (!result)
3948 goto error;
3949 for (i = 0; i < map1->n; ++i)
3950 for (j = 0; j < map2->n; ++j) {
3951 struct isl_basic_map *part;
3952 part = isl_basic_map_sum(
3953 isl_basic_map_copy(map1->p[i]),
3954 isl_basic_map_copy(map2->p[j]));
3955 if (isl_basic_map_is_empty(part))
3956 isl_basic_map_free(part);
3957 else
3958 result = isl_map_add_basic_map(result, part);
3959 if (!result)
3960 goto error;
3961 }
3962 isl_map_free(map1);
3963 isl_map_free(map2);
3964 return result;
3965error:
3966 isl_map_free(map1);
3967 isl_map_free(map2);
3968 return NULL((void*)0);
3969}

4035/* Given a basic map A -> f(A) and an integer d, construct a basic map
4036 * A -> floor(f(A)/d).
4037 */
4038struct isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_floordiv(struct isl_basic_map *bmap,
4039 isl_int d)
4040{
4041 unsigned n_in, n_out, nparam, total, pos;
4042 struct isl_basic_map *result = NULL((void*)0);
4043 struct isl_dim_map *dim_map;
4044 int i;
4045
4046 if (!bmap)
4047 return NULL((void*)0);
4048
4049 nparam = isl_basic_map_n_param(bmap);
4050 n_in = isl_basic_map_n_in(bmap);
4051 n_out = isl_basic_map_n_out(bmap);
4052
4053 total = nparam + n_in + n_out + bmap->n_div + n_out;
4054 dim_map = isl_dim_map_alloc(bmap->ctx, total);
4055 isl_dim_map_dim(dim_map, bmap->dim, isl_dim_param, pos = 0);
4056 isl_dim_map_dim(dim_map, bmap->dim, isl_dim_in, pos += nparam);
4057 isl_dim_map_div(dim_map, bmap, pos += n_in + n_out);
4058 isl_dim_map_dim(dim_map, bmap->dim, isl_dim_out, pos += bmap->n_div);
4059
4060 result = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(isl_space_copy(bmap->dim),
4061 bmap->n_div + n_out,
4062 bmap->n_eq, bmap->n_ineq + 2 * n_out);
4063 result = isl_basic_map_add_constraints_dim_map(result, bmap, dim_map);
4064 result = add_divs(result, n_out);
4065 for (i = 0; i < n_out; ++i) {
4066 int j;
4067 j = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(result);
4068 if (j < 0)
4069 goto error;
4070 isl_seq_clr(result->ineq[j], 1+total);
4071 isl_int_neg(result->ineq[j][1+nparam+n_in+i], d)isl_sioimath_neg((result->ineq[j][1+nparam+n_in+i]), *(d));
4072 isl_int_set_si(result->ineq[j][1+pos+i], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((result->ineq[j][1+pos+i]), 1);
4073 j = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(result);
4074 if (j < 0)
4075 goto error;
4076 isl_seq_clr(result->ineq[j], 1+total);
4077 isl_int_set(result->ineq[j][1+nparam+n_in+i], d)isl_sioimath_set((result->ineq[j][1+nparam+n_in+i]), *(d));
4078 isl_int_set_si(result->ineq[j][1+pos+i], -1)isl_sioimath_set_si((result->ineq[j][1+pos+i]), -1);
4079 isl_int_sub_ui(result->ineq[j][0], d, 1)isl_sioimath_sub_ui((result->ineq[j][0]), *(d), 1);
4080 }
4081
4082 result = isl_basic_map_simplify(result);
4083 return isl_basic_map_finalize(result);
4084error:
4085 isl_basic_map_free(result);
4086 return NULL((void*)0);
4087}

4134static struct isl_basic_map *var_equal(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned pos)
4135{

4143 nparam = isl_basic_map_n_param(bmap);
4144 n_in = isl_basic_map_n_in(bmap);
4145 isl_seq_clr(bmap->eq[i], 1 + isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap));
4146 isl_int_set_si(bmap->eq[i][1+nparam+pos], -1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->eq[i][1+nparam+pos]), -1);
4147 isl_int_set_si(bmap->eq[i][1+nparam+n_in+pos], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->eq[i][1+nparam+n_in+pos]), 1);
4148 return isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
4149error:
4150 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
4151 return NULL((void*)0);
4152}

4260 */

4323static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *map_lex_lte_first(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dims,
4324 unsigned n, int equal)
4325{
4326 struct isl_map *map;
4327 int i;
4328
4329 if (n == 0 && equal)
4330 return isl_map_universe(dims);
4331
4332 map = isl_map_alloc_space(isl_space_copy(dims), n, ISL_MAP_DISJOINT(1 << 0));
4333
4334 for (i = 0; i + 1 < n; ++i)
4335 map = isl_map_add_basic_map(map,
4336 isl_basic_map_less_at(isl_space_copy(dims), i));
4337 if (n > 0) {
4338 if (equal)
4339 map = isl_map_add_basic_map(map,
4340 isl_basic_map_less_or_equal_at(dims, n - 1));
4341 else
4342 map = isl_map_add_basic_map(map,
4343 isl_basic_map_less_at(dims, n - 1));
4344 } else
4345 isl_space_free(dims);
4346
4347 return map;
4348}

4350static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *map_lex_lte(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dims, int equal)
4351{
4352 if (!dims)
4353 return NULL((void*)0);
4354 return map_lex_lte_first(dims, dims->n_out, equal);
4355}

4377static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *map_lex_gte_first(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dims,
4378 unsigned n, int equal)
4379{
4380 struct isl_map *map;
4381 int i;
4382
4383 if (n == 0 && equal)
4384 return isl_map_universe(dims);
4385
4386 map = isl_map_alloc_space(isl_space_copy(dims), n, ISL_MAP_DISJOINT(1 << 0));

4395 else
4396 map = isl_map_add_basic_map(map,
4397 isl_basic_map_more_at(dims, n - 1));
4398 } else
4399 isl_space_free(dims);
4400

4511__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_from_basic_set(
4512 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dim)
4513{
4514 struct isl_basic_map *bmap;
4515
4516 bset = isl_basic_set_cow(bset);
4517 if (!bset || !dim)
4518 goto error;
4519
4520 isl_assert(bset->ctx, isl_space_compatible(bset->dim, dim), goto error)do { if (isl_space_compatible(bset->dim, dim)) break; do {
isl_handle_error(bset->ctx, isl_error_unknown, "Assertion \""
"isl_space_compatible(bset->dim, dim)" "\" failed", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_map.c"
, 4520); goto error; } while (0); } while (0);
4521 isl_space_free(bset->dim);
4522 bmap = (struct isl_basic_map *) bset;
4523 bmap->dim = dim;
4524 return isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
4525error:
4526 isl_basic_set_free(bset);
4527 isl_space_free(dim);
4528 return NULL((void*)0);
4529}
4530
4531/* For a div d = floor(f/m), add the constraint
4532 *
4533 * f - m d >= 0
4534 */
4535static int add_upper_div_constraint(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
4536 unsigned pos, isl_int *div)
4537{
4538 int i;
4539 unsigned total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
4540
4541 i = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(bmap);
4542 if (i < 0)
4543 return -1;
4544 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->ineq[i], div + 1, 1 + total);
4545 isl_int_neg(bmap->ineq[i][1 + pos], div[0])isl_sioimath_neg((bmap->ineq[i][1 + pos]), *(div[0]));
4546
4547 return 0;
4548}
4549
4550/* For a div d = floor(f/m), add the constraint
4551 *
4552 * -(f-(m-1)) + m d >= 0
4553 */
4554static int add_lower_div_constraint(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
4555 unsigned pos, isl_int *div)
4556{
4557 int i;
4558 unsigned total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
4559
4560 i = isl_basic_map_alloc_inequality(bmap);
4561 if (i < 0)
4562 return -1;
4563 isl_seq_neg(bmap->ineq[i], div + 1, 1 + total);
4564 isl_int_set(bmap->ineq[i][1 + pos], div[0])isl_sioimath_set((bmap->ineq[i][1 + pos]), *(div[0]));
4565 isl_int_add(bmap->ineq[i][0], bmap->ineq[i][0], bmap->ineq[i][1 + pos])isl_sioimath_add((bmap->ineq[i][0]), *(bmap->ineq[i][0]
), *(bmap->ineq[i][1 + pos]));
4566 isl_int_sub_ui(bmap->ineq[i][0], bmap->ineq[i][0], 1)isl_sioimath_sub_ui((bmap->ineq[i][0]), *(bmap->ineq[i]
[0]), 1);
4567
4568 return 0;
4569}
4570
4571/* For a div d = floor(f/m), add the constraints
4572 *
4573 * f - m d >= 0
4574 * -(f-(m-1)) + m d >= 0
4575 *
4576 * Note that the second constraint is the negation of
4577 *
4578 * f - m d >= m
4579 */
4580int isl_basic_map_add_div_constraints_var(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
4581 unsigned pos, isl_int *div)
4582{
4583 if (add_upper_div_constraint(bmap, pos, div) < 0)
4584 return -1;
4585 if (add_lower_div_constraint(bmap, pos, div) < 0)
4586 return -1;
4587 return 0;
4588}
4589
4590int isl_basic_set_add_div_constraints_var(__isl_keep isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset,
4591 unsigned pos, isl_int *div)
4592{
4593 return isl_basic_map_add_div_constraints_var((isl_basic_map *)bset,
4594 pos, div);
4595}
4596
4597int isl_basic_map_add_div_constraints(struct isl_basic_map *bmap, unsigned div)
4598{
4599 unsigned total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
4600 unsigned div_pos = total - bmap->n_div + div;
4601
4602 return isl_basic_map_add_div_constraints_var(bmap, div_pos,
4603 bmap->div[div]);
4604}
4605
4606/* For each known div d = floor(f/m), add the constraints
4607 *
4608 * f - m d >= 0
4609 * -(f-(m-1)) + m d >= 0
4610 *
4611 * Remove duplicate constraints in case of some these div constraints
4612 * already appear in "bmap".
4613 */
4614__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_add_known_div_constraints(
4615 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap)
4616{
4617 unsigned n_div;
4618
4619 if (!bmap)
4620 return NULL((void*)0);
4621 n_div = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_div);
4622 if (n_div == 0)
4623 return bmap;
4624
4625 bmap = add_known_div_constraints(bmap);
4626 bmap = isl_basic_map_remove_duplicate_constraints(bmap, NULL((void*)0), 0);
4627 bmap = isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
4628 return bmap;
4629}
4630
4631/* Add the div constraint of sign "sign" for div "div" of "bmap".
4632 *
4633 * In particular, if this div is of the form d = floor(f/m),
4634 * then add the constraint
4635 *
4636 * f - m d >= 0
4637 *
4638 * if sign < 0 or the constraint
4639 *
4640 * -(f-(m-1)) + m d >= 0
4641 *
4642 * if sign > 0.
4643 */
4644int isl_basic_map_add_div_constraint(__isl_keep isl_basic_map *bmap,
4645 unsigned div, int sign)
4646{
4647 unsigned total;
4648 unsigned div_pos;
4649
4650 if (!bmap)
4651 return -1;
4652
4653 total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
4654 div_pos = total - bmap->n_div + div;
4655
4656 if (sign < 0)
4657 return add_upper_div_constraint(bmap, div_pos, bmap->div[div]);
4658 else
4659 return add_lower_div_constraint(bmap, div_pos, bmap->div[div]);
4660}
4661
4662int isl_basic_set_add_div_constraints(struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset, unsigned div)
4663{
4664 return isl_basic_map_add_div_constraints(bset, div);
4665}
4666
4667struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_underlying_set(
4668 struct isl_basic_map *bmap)
4669{
4670 if (!bmap)
4671 goto error;
4672 if (bmap->dim->nparam == 0 && bmap->dim->n_in == 0 &&
4673 bmap->n_div == 0 &&
4674 !isl_space_is_named_or_nested(bmap->dim, isl_dim_in) &&
4675 !isl_space_is_named_or_nested(bmap->dim, isl_dim_out))
4676 return (struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *)bmap;
4677 bmap = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap);
4678 if (!bmap)
4679 goto error;
4680 bmap->dim = isl_space_underlying(bmap->dim, bmap->n_div);
4681 if (!bmap->dim)
4682 goto error;
4683 bmap->extra -= bmap->n_div;
4684 bmap->n_div = 0;
4685 bmap = isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
4686 return (struct isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *)bmap;
4687error:
4688 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
4689 return NULL((void*)0);
4690}

4698/* Replace each element in "list" by the result of applying
4699 * isl_basic_map_underlying_set to the element.
4700 */
4701__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_set_listisl_basic_map_list *isl_basic_map_list_underlying_set(
4702 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map_list *list)
4703{
4704 int i, n;
4705
4706 if (!list)
4707 return NULL((void*)0);
4708
4709 n = isl_basic_map_list_n_basic_map(list);
4710 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
4711 isl_basic_map *bmap;
4712 isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset;
4713
4714 bmap = isl_basic_map_list_get_basic_map(list, i);
4715 bset = isl_basic_set_underlying_set(bmap);
4716 list = isl_basic_set_list_set_basic_set(list, i, bset);
4717 }
4718
4719 return list;
4720}

4865/* Replace the space of "bmap" by "space".
4866 *
4867 * If the space of "bmap" is identical to "space" (including the identifiers
4868 * of the input and output dimensions), then simply return the original input.
4869 */
4870__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_reset_space(
4871 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *space)
4872{
4873 isl_bool equal;
4874
4875 if (!bmap)
4876 goto error;
4877 equal = isl_space_is_equal(bmap->dim, space);
4878 if (equal >= 0 && equal)
4879 equal = isl_space_match(bmap->dim, isl_dim_in,
4880 space, isl_dim_in);
4881 if (equal >= 0 && equal)
4882 equal = isl_space_match(bmap->dim, isl_dim_out,
4883 space, isl_dim_out);
4884 if (equal < 0)
4885 goto error;
4886 if (equal) {
4887 isl_space_free(space);
4888 return bmap;
4889 }
4890 bmap = isl_basic_map_cow(bmap);
4891 if (!bmap || !space)
4892 goto error;
4893
4894 isl_space_free(bmap->dim);
4895 bmap->dim = space;
4896
4897 bmap = isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
4898
4899 return bmap;
4900error:
4901 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
4902 isl_space_free(space);
4903 return NULL((void*)0);
4904}

4907 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dim)
4908{
4909 return (isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *)isl_basic_map_reset_space((isl_basic_map *)bset,
4910 dim);
4911}

4913__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *isl_map_reset_space(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_map *map,
4914 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dim)
4915{
4916 int i;
4917
4918 map = isl_map_cow(map);
4919 if (!map || !dim)
4920 goto error;
4921
4922 for (i = 0; i < map->n; ++i) {
4923 map->p[i] = isl_basic_map_reset_space(map->p[i],
4924 isl_space_copy(dim));
4925 if (!map->p[i])
4926 goto error;
4927 }
4928 isl_space_free(map->dim);
4929 map->dim = dim;
4930
4931 return map;
4932error:
4933 isl_map_free(map);
4934 isl_space_free(dim);
4935 return NULL((void*)0);
4936}

5061
5062__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_domain_map(
5063 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap)
5064{
5065 int i, k;
5066 isl_space *dim;
5067 isl_basic_map *domain;
5068 int nparam, n_in, n_out;
5069 unsigned total;
5070
5071 nparam = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_param);
5072 n_in = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_in);
5073 n_out = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_out);
5074
5075 dim = isl_space_from_range(isl_space_domain(isl_basic_map_get_space(bmap)));
5076 domain = isl_basic_map_universe(dim);
5077
5078 bmap = isl_basic_map_from_domain(isl_basic_map_wrap(bmap));
5079 bmap = isl_basic_map_apply_range(bmap, domain);
5080 bmap = isl_basic_map_extend_constraints(bmap, n_in, 0);
5081
5082 total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
5083
5084 for (i = 0; i < n_in; ++i) {
5085 k = isl_basic_map_alloc_equality(bmap);
5086 if (k < 0)
5087 goto error;
5088 isl_seq_clr(bmap->eq[k], 1 + total);
5089 isl_int_set_si(bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + i], -1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + i]), -1);
5090 isl_int_set_si(bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + n_in + n_out + i], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + n_in + n_out
+ i]), 1);
5091 }
5092
5093 bmap = isl_basic_map_gauss(bmap, NULL((void*)0));
5094 return isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
5095error:
5096 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
5097 return NULL((void*)0);
5098}
5099
5100__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_range_map(
5101 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_map *bmap)
5102{
5103 int i, k;
5104 isl_space *dim;
5105 isl_basic_map *range;
5106 int nparam, n_in, n_out;
5107 unsigned total;
5108
5109 nparam = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_param);
5110 n_in = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_in);
5111 n_out = isl_basic_map_dim(bmap, isl_dim_out);
5112
5113 dim = isl_space_from_range(isl_space_range(isl_basic_map_get_space(bmap)));
5114 range = isl_basic_map_universe(dim);
5115
5116 bmap = isl_basic_map_from_domain(isl_basic_map_wrap(bmap));
5117 bmap = isl_basic_map_apply_range(bmap, range);
5118 bmap = isl_basic_map_extend_constraints(bmap, n_out, 0);
5119
5120 total = isl_basic_map_total_dim(bmap);
5121
5122 for (i = 0; i < n_out; ++i) {
5123 k = isl_basic_map_alloc_equality(bmap);
5124 if (k < 0)
5125 goto error;
5126 isl_seq_clr(bmap->eq[k], 1 + total);
5127 isl_int_set_si(bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + n_in + i], -1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + n_in + i]), -
1);
5128 isl_int_set_si(bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + n_in + n_out + i], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((bmap->eq[k][1 + nparam + n_in + n_out
+ i]), 1);
5129 }
5130
5131 bmap = isl_basic_map_gauss(bmap, NULL((void*)0));
5132 return isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
5133error:
5134 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
5135 return NULL((void*)0);
5136}
